us.\", \"from\": 4578, \"to\": 4633, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theSurfrider Foundation's Lionel Cheylus\", \"from\": 4592, \"to\": 4632}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He pointed out that although Surfrider does scientific water-quality evaluation, it does so in accordance with theEuropean Bathing Water Directive, which zeroes in on fecal bacteria, but doesnotrequire testing for pesticides, pharmaceuticals, and other chemical pollution.\", \"from\": 4634, \"to\": 4906, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4663, \"end\": 4672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surfrider\", \"score\": 0.8020135056820301, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Surfrider\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surfrider\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surfrider\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"scientific water-quality evaluation\", \"from\": 4678, \"to\": 4713}, {\"ngram\": \"accordance\", \"from\": 4729, \"to\": 4739}, {\"ngram\": \"theEuropean Bathing Water Directive\", \"from\": 4745, \"to\": 4780}, {\"ngram\": \"fecal bacteria\", \"from\": 4801, \"to\": 4815}, {\"ngram\": \"pesticides\", \"from\": 4848, \"to\": 4858}, {\"ngram\": \"pharmaceuticals\", \"from\": 4860, \"to\": 4875}, {\"ngram\": \"other chemical pollution\", \"from\": 4881, \"to\": 4905}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French government may be testing for those chemicals, but officials are not willing to share their data and protocols with the public.\", \"from\": 4907, \"to\": 5045, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4911, \"end\": 4917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.97747409681423, \"rank\": 0.019646641315390855, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those chemicals\", \"from\": 4948, \"to\": 4963}, {\"ngram\": \"officials\", \"from\": 4969, \"to\": 4978}, {\"ngram\": \"their data\", \"from\": 5004, \"to\": 5014}, {\"ngram\": \"protocols\", \"from\": 5019, \"to\": 5028}, {\"ngram\": \"the public\", \"from\": 5034, \"to\": 5044}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cheylus said, \\\"Transparency is really important in these kinds of issues.\\\"\", \"from\": 5046, \"to\": 5120, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Cheylus\", \"from\": 5046, \"to\": 5053}, {\"ngram\": \"Transparency\", \"from\": 5061, \"to\": 5073}, {\"ngram\": \"these kinds\", \"from\": 5097, \"to\": 5108}, {\"ngram\": \"issues\", \"from\": 5112, \"to\": 5118}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He added, \\\"I think they could be more transparent and give more information sometimes.\\u2026 They could really improve.\\\"\", \"from\": 5121, \"to\": 5236, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more information\", \"from\": 5180, \"to\": 5196}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Until then, he noted, it's impossible to know the full effects of the water on swimmers, including Olympic athletes.\", \"from\": 5237, \"to\": 5353, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the full effects\", \"from\": 5283, \"to\": 5299}, {\"ngram\": \"the water\", \"from\": 5303, \"to\": 5312}, {\"ngram\": \"swimmers\", \"from\": 5316, \"to\": 5324}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic athletes\", \"from\": 5336, \"to\": 5352}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee often sloganizes with phrases like \\\"Athletes First,\\\" but if the Seine does not meet the safety standards, thebackup planis to postpone events in the river, which organizersannouncedon Tuesday that they will, in fact, have to do.\", \"from\": 5355, \"to\": 5619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5359, \"end\": 5390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 5455, \"end\": 5460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0390266255609102e-14, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"phrases\", \"from\": 5413, \"to\": 5420}, {\"ngram\": \"Athletes\", \"from\": 5427, \"to\": 5435}, {\"ngram\": \"the safety standards\", \"from\": 5475, \"to\": 5495}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 5526, \"to\": 5532}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 5536, \"to\": 5545}, {\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 5602, \"to\": 5606}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If that does not resolve the issue, then Olympic organizers will take the extreme action of eliminating the swimming portion of the triathlon, leaving only biking and running.\", \"from\": 5620, \"to\": 5795, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the issue\", \"from\": 5645, \"to\": 5654}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic organizers\", \"from\": 5661, \"to\": 5679}, {\"ngram\": \"the extreme action\", \"from\": 5690, \"to\": 5708}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimming portion\", \"from\": 5724, \"to\": 5744}, {\"ngram\": \"the triathlon\", \"from\": 5748, \"to\": 5761}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To say that this would disfigure the competition for which these athletes have trained is to make a massive understatement.\", \"from\": 5796, \"to\": 5919, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 5829, \"to\": 5844}, {\"ngram\": \"these athletes\", \"from\": 5855, \"to\": 5869}, {\"ngram\": \"a massive understatement\", \"from\": 5894, \"to\": 5918}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Veteran sports reporter Martyn Zieglercalledit \\\"farcical.\\\"\", \"from\": 5920, \"to\": 5978, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Veteran sports reporter Martyn Zieglercalledit\", \"from\": 5920, \"to\": 5966}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It sounds like athletes are coming in closer to last than first.\", \"from\": 5979, \"to\": 6043, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 5994, \"to\": 6002}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But when activists fromExtinction Rebellionand other environmental groups tried to draw attention to the safety of the Seine, the response was intense repression to protect the Olympic spectacle.\", \"from\": 6045, \"to\": 6240, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6164, \"end\": 6169, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0390266255609102e-14, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"activists\", \"from\": 6054, \"to\": 6063}, {\"ngram\": \"Rebellionand other environmental groups\", \"from\": 6079, \"to\": 6118}, {\"ngram\": \"attention\", \"from\": 6133, \"to\": 6142}, {\"ngram\": \"the safety\", \"from\": 6146, \"to\": 6156}, {\"ngram\": \"the response\", \"from\": 6171, \"to\": 6183}, {\"ngram\": \"intense repression\", \"from\": 6188, \"to\": 6206}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic spectacle\", \"from\": 6218, \"to\": 6239}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We asked Orr whether someday in the near future the Olympics will not be able to be staged because of the climate.\", \"from\": 6242, \"to\": 6356, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Orr\", \"from\": 6251, \"to\": 6254}, {\"ngram\": \"the near future\", \"from\": 6274, \"to\": 6289}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 6290, \"to\": 6302}, {\"ngram\": \"the climate\", \"from\": 6344, \"to\": 6355}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her response was sobering: \\\"I think that's going to happen on the Winter [Olympics] side sooner than we think.\", \"from\": 6357, \"to\": 6467, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her response\", \"from\": 6357, \"to\": 6369}, {\"ngram\": \"the Winter [Olympics\", \"from\": 6419, \"to\": 6439}, {\"ngram\": \"side\", \"from\": 6441, \"to\": 6445}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I think we will get through the next couple rounds.\", \"from\": 6468, \"to\": 6519, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the next couple\", \"from\": 6496, \"to\": 6511}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But\\u2026we are going to see places be too hot to host the Winter Games.\", \"from\": 6520, \"to\": 6587, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"places\", \"from\": 6544, \"to\": 6550}, {\"ngram\": \"the Winter Games\", \"from\": 6570, \"to\": 6586}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And on the Summer [Olympics] side, a 2016 study out of the UK said actually, there is maybe a dozen cities across the Northern Hemisphere that will be tenable to host the Games by mid-century, if it continues to be in July and August.\\u2026 Something's got to give.\\\"\", \"from\": 6588, \"to\": 6849, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6647, \"end\": 6649, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999942046998, \"rank\": 5.776918578393894e-09, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Summer [Olympics] side\", \"from\": 6595, \"to\": 6621}, {\"ngram\": \"a 2016 study\", \"from\": 6623, \"to\": 6635}, {\"ngram\": \"a dozen cities\", \"from\": 6680, \"to\": 6694}, {\"ngram\": \"the Northern Hemisphere\", \"from\": 6702, \"to\": 6725}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 6755, \"to\": 6764}, {\"ngram\": \"mid\", \"from\": 6768, \"to\": 6771}, {\"ngram\": \"century\", \"from\": 6772, \"to\": 6779}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 6806, \"to\": 6810}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 6815, \"to\": 6821}, {\"ngram\": \"Something\", \"from\": 6824, \"to\": 6833}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peter KornbluhandWilliam M. LeoGrande Column/Sasha Abramsky David Faris Amber Husain The choice for the future of the Olympics and other mega-events is simple: Either they will have to be radically rethought and reconfigured to reduce their carbon footprint, or they must cease to continue as the number of cities dwindles that are safe for athletes and fans.\", \"from\": 6851, \"to\": 7214, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6851, \"end\": 6856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spider-Man\", \"score\": 0.9999999981919245, \"rank\": 1.8035866404001955e-09, \"text\": \"Peter\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spider-Man\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spider-Man\"}, {\"begin\": 6897, \"end\": 6911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sasha_Abramsky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sasha Abramsky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sasha_Abramsky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sasha_Abramsky\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The choice\", \"from\": 6936, \"to\": 6946}, {\"ngram\": \"the future\", \"from\": 6951, \"to\": 6961}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 6965, \"to\": 6977}, {\"ngram\": \"other mega\", \"from\": 6982, \"to\": 6992}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 6993, \"to\": 6999}, {\"ngram\": \"their carbon footprint\", \"from\": 7086, \"to\": 7108}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 7144, \"to\": 7154}, {\"ngram\": \"cities dwindles\", \"from\": 7158, \"to\": 7173}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 7192, \"to\": 7200}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 7205, \"to\": 7209}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The choice for the future of sports mega-events is clear: real-deal sustainability or extinction.\", \"from\": 7215, \"to\": 7312, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The choice\", \"from\": 7215, \"to\": 7225}, {\"ngram\": \"the future\", \"from\": 7230, \"to\": 7240}, {\"ngram\": \"sports mega\", \"from\": 7244, \"to\": 7255}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 7256, \"to\": 7262}, {\"ngram\": \"real-deal sustainability\", \"from\": 7273, \"to\": 7297}, {\"ngram\": \"extinction\", \"from\": 7301, \"to\": 7311}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even before February 28, the reasons for Donald Trump's imploding approval rating were abundantly clear: untrammeled corruption and personal enrichment to the tune of billions of dollars during an affordability crisis, a foreign policy guided only by his own derelict sense of morality, and the deployment of a murderous campaign of occupation, detention, and deportation on American streets.\", \"from\": 7314, \"to\": 7706, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7355, \"end\": 7367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.999933548171379, \"rank\": 6.645624507257869e-05, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 7689, \"end\": 7697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.404127332671286e-19, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"February\", \"from\": 7326, \"to\": 7334}, {\"ngram\": \"the reasons\", \"from\": 7339, \"to\": 7350}, {\"ngram\": \"untrammeled corruption\", \"from\": 7419, \"to\": 7441}, {\"ngram\": \"personal enrichment\", \"from\": 7446, \"to\": 7465}, {\"ngram\": \"the tune\", \"from\": 7469, \"to\": 7477}, {\"ngram\": \"billions\", \"from\": 7481, \"to\": 7489}, {\"ngram\": \"dollars\", \"from\": 7493, \"to\": 7500}, {\"ngram\": \"an affordability crisis\", \"from\": 7508, \"to\": 7531}, {\"ngram\": \"a foreign policy\", \"from\": 7533, \"to\": 7549}, {\"ngram\": \"his own derelict sense\", \"from\": 7565, \"to\": 7587}, {\"ngram\": \"morality\", \"from\": 7591, \"to\": 7599}, {\"ngram\": \"the deployment\", \"from\": 7605, \"to\": 7619}, {\"ngram\": \"a murderous campaign\", \"from\": 7623, \"to\": 7643}, {\"n